MNUMBER 352
UNIQUE
NAME Blackshroud
HUMAN
BODY 500
EXTRABODY 10
ATTACK1 440
DEFENSE 380
STRENGTH 85
STRATEGY 501
IMMUNITY 0 0
IMMUNITY 3 1
IMMUNITY 4 1
IMMUNITY 5 1
IMMUNITY 6 0
IMMUNITY 7 0
WEAPON 32 404 100
WEAPONPLUS 11
ARMOR 50
DISCORPORATE
ETERNAL
GENDER 0
RESIST 380
SPEED 1
*DESCRIPTION_START
You see a tall aelven warrior, skilled in the arts of combat. He radiates an aura of calm authority, and is swathed in black cloths from head to toe. A rapier, darkened for concealment, is his only weapon.
*DESCRIPTION_END
HIDESKILL 72
SPECUSE 8
SPECUSES 4
SPECBASE 7
SPECDMG 14
SPECDMGTYPE SLASH
TEXX %s flings a handful of razor-sharp crystal slivers at %s!
TEXH The Blackshroud eyes you calmly.
TEXD bows deeply before you, acknowledging your accomplishment, then fades into the shadows.
;
NUMBER 2436
NAME Next to a Huge Tree
FOREST
CALL 33
REGION 151
*DESCRIPTION_START
This part of the grasslands is dominated by an enormous tree which rises majestically from the ground. Its thick branches cast deep shadows and there is no telling what its depths conceal. The leaves shimmer with the breath of the slight and constant breeze that travels through this hollow.
*DESCRIPTION_END
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
DAY_LIGHT
ITEM 0 229  ADJ1=163  ADJ2=216 ; a huge oak tree
ITEM 9 693
EXTEND 0 whose spreading leaves provide pleasant shade
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
The gnarled bark of this immense tree is knotted and folded back upon itself several times over, causing it to look truly ancient. the knotted bark of the beautiful pillar seems to twist around its trunk in a dazzling pattern of age and elegance. As you look closely, each crevice and mark seems to resemble the visage of something living. This is truly a remarkable and special force within these woods.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT O 129
IFSAY Abastoli_Ienna
 IFCARRY 1861 -1
  IFITEM -1 WORN
   SPELL 250 0
   ECHO PLAYER The tree takes you up in its boughs, lifting you away.
   ECHO OTHERS The huge tree lowers a branch around %N, and lifts %i away.
   MOVEGROUP 2437
  ELSE
   ECHO PLAYER You feel threatened without the protection of your shroud.
   ECHO OTHERS %n looks about, eyes wide in apprehension.
  ENDIF
 ELSE
  SPELL 250 0
  ECHO ALL The tree creaks and groans before you.
  DAMAGEPLR CRUSH 299 A large branch from the tree strikes you!
  ECHO OTHERS %N is struck by a large branch!
  MOVEGROUP 129
  POSITION LAY
  AFFECT 129
  ECHO OTHERS %n is knocked into the area!
 ENDIF
ENDIF 
;
IFENTRY 
 IFCARRY 1861 -1
  ECHO PLAYER You feel the warmth of the woods kindling a fire in your spirit.
 ELSE
  ECHO ALL The tree creaks and groans before you with something akin to anger!
  PLREVENT 0
  CONTPLREVENT
  IFVAR MISTFORM ! 1
   SPELL 250 0
   DAMAGEPLR CRUSH 299 A large branch from the tree strikes you!
   ECHO OTHERS %N is struck by a large branch!
   MOVEGROUP 129
   POSITION LAY
   AFFECT 129
   ECHO OTHERS %n is knocked into the area!
  ELSE
   ECHO PLAYER A gust of air from within the boughs of the tree sends you sailing skyward!
   MOVEGROUP 129                                                                       
  ENDIF
 ENDIF
ENDIF 
;
INUMBER 1861
NAME 1532
WEIGHT 1
VOLUME 3
WORN_DON
SUBSTANCE INDESTRUCTABLE
MISC
CONTAINER UNDER
INTERIOR 12
TURNABLE
*DESCRIPTION_START
The shroud is a long strip of rectangular, Aelfen silk. The weave of the braided silk is so tight that no spaces show between the nearly invisible threads and yet the garment still weighs nearly nothing. You suspect that it would protect against water and condensation while still breathing adequately. One side is a muted forest green while the other is a completely colorless shade.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFPREVERB GO -1
 CLEARVERB
 IFITEM -1 WORN
  IFVAR RNUM = 129
   ECHO PLAYER You gaze into the depths of your shroud, thinking about the great fallen aelfen warriors of times past as the trees part, allowing you passage to an inner, hidden grove.
   ECHO OTHERS %n steps behind a stand of trees.
   MOVEGROUP 2436
   AFFECT 2436
   ECHO OTHERS %n steps out from behind a stand of trees.
  ELSE
   ECHO PLAYER You can't seem to do that here.
  ENDIF
 ELSE
  ECHO PLAYER You hold up the shroud and attempt to step into it, succeeding only in entangling your legs and falling to the ground.
  ECHO OTHERS As %n attempts to walk into a shroud %s becomes entangled and falls to the ground looking rather stupid.
  POSITION LAY
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB WEAR -1
 IFVAR ITEMVAL1 ! INTNUM3
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER As you manipulate %a it dissolves into black vapor and drifts through your fingers.
  ECHO OTHERS As %n manipulates %a it dissolves into vapor and drifts silently through %h fingers.
  REMOVEITEM -1
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB TURN -1
 CLEARVERB
 IFVAR ITEMVAL1 = INTNUM3
  IFVAR ITEMADJ1 = 133
   SETITEMADJ -1 1 -1
   SETITEMADJ -1 2 -1
   IFVAR ITEMVAL5 > 199
    SETITEMADJ -1 3 25
    ECHO PLAYER You flip %a around with a snap, exposing the ebony silk side of it.
    ECHO OTHERS %n flips %a around %h body with a snap, exposing the ebony silk side of it.
    IFVAR ORG = 27
     SETITEMADJ -1 2 713
    ENDIF
   ELSE
    IFVAR ITEMVAL5 > 99
     SETITEMADJ -1 3 150
     ECHO PLAYER You flip %a around with a snap, exposing the stormcloud gray silk side of it.
     ECHO OTHERS %n flips %a around %h body with a snap, exposing the stormcloud gray silk side of it.
     IFVAR ORG = 27
      SETITEMADJ -1 2 713
     ENDIF
    ELSE
     IFVAR ITEMVAL5 > 49
      SETITEMADJ -1 3 292
      ECHO PLAYER You flip %a around with a snap, exposing the shimmering silver side of it.
      ECHO OTHERS %n flips %a around %h body with a snap, exposing the shimmering silver side of it.
      IFVAR ORG = 27
       SETITEMADJ -1 2 713
      ENDIF
     ELSE
      SETITEMADJ -1 3 347
      ECHO PLAYER You flip %a around with a snap, exposing the virgin white silk side of it.
      ECHO OTHERS %n flips %a around %h body with a snap, exposing the virgin white silk side of it.
      IFVAR ORG = 27
       SETITEMADJ -1 2 713
      ENDIF
     ENDIF
    ENDIF
   ENDIF
  ELSE
   SETITEMADJ -1 1 133
   SETITEMADJ -1 2 152
   SETITEMADJ -1 3 -1
   ECHO PLAYER You flip %a around with a snap, exposing the forest green silk side of it.
   ECHO OTHERS %n flips %a around %h body with a snap, exposing the forest green silk side of it.
  ENDIF
 ELSE
  ECHO PLAYER As you manipulate %a it dissolves into black vapor and drifts through your fingers.
  ECHO OTHERS As %n manipulates %a it dissolves into vapor and drifts silently through %h fingers.
  REMOVEITEM -1
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB PULL -1
 CLEARVERB
 IFVAR ITEMVAL1 = INTNUM3
  IFITEM -1 WORN
   ECHO PLAYER You drape %a tightly around your body, covering your face with the trailing ends.
   ECHO OTHERS %n drapes %a more tightly around %h body, covering %h face with the trailing ends.
  ELSE
   ECHO PLAYER With a flick of your wrist %a unfurls to its full length.
   ECHO OTHERS With a flick of %n's wrist %a unfurls to its full length.
  ENDIF
 ELSE
  ECHO PLAYER As you manipulate %a it dissolves into black vapor and drifts through your fingers.
  ECHO OTHERS As %n manipulates %a it dissolves into vapor and drifts silently through %h fingers.
  REMOVEITEM -1
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB PUSH -1
 CLEARVERB
 IFVAR ITEMVAL1 = INTNUM3
  IFITEM -1 WORN
   ECHO PLAYER You push %a back from your head, exposing your face.
   ECHO OTHERS %N pushes %a back from %h head, exposing %h face.
  ELSE
   ECHO PLAYER With an intricate gesture you gather %a into an impossibly small packet.
   ECHO OTHERS With an intricate gesture, %n gathers %a into an impossible small packet.
  ENDIF
 ELSE
  ECHO PLAYER As you manipulate %a it dissolves into black vapor and drifts through your fingers.
  ECHO OTHERS As %n manipulates %a it dissolves into vapor and drifts silently through %h fingers.
  REMOVEITEM -1
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB CAST -1
 CLEARVERB
 IFVAR ITEMVAL1 = INTNUM3
  IFVAR INTNUM57 = 0
   ECHO PLAYER You send your soul out to the spirits of the wood with no visible response.
   ECHO OTHERS As the smells of the forest seem to blow through the area on the wings of a gentle breeze, 
   ECHO OTHERS %n throws %h shoulders back as if trying to escape the bounds of flesh before returning to %iself with a shudder.
  ENDIF
  IFVAR INTNUM57 = 1
   ECHO PLAYER You beseech mighty Wolf for his aid!
   ECHO OTHERS %n calls out in the language of the wolves.
   PLREVENT 0
   CONTPLREVENT
   ECHO PLAYER The power of Wolf flows through you!
   SPELL 537 0
  ENDIF
  IFVAR INTNUM57 = 2
   IFVAR ITEMVAL3 ! TIM
    ECHO PLAYER You beseech cunning Raven for his aid!
    ECHO OTHERS %n calls out in the cawing language of the ravens.
    SETITEMVAL -1 3 TIM
    PLREVENT 0
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER You are filled with the agile cunning of the Raven.
    SPELL 514 0
   ELSE
    ECHO PLAYER Nothing seems to happen.
   ENDIF
  ENDIF
  IFVAR INTNUM57 = 4
   IFVAR ITEMVAL3 ! TIM
    ECHO PLAYER You beseech Falcon for his aid!
    ECHO OTHERS %n calls out in the piercing language of the falcon.
    SETITEMVAL -1 3 TIM
    PLREVENT 0
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER You are filled with the keen mastery of Falcon.
    SPELL 347 0
   ELSE
    ECHO PLAYER Nothing seems to happen.
   ENDIF
  ENDIF
  IFVAR INTNUM57 = 7
   ECHO PLAYER You beseech nocturnal Bat for his aid!
   ECHO OTHERS %n calls out in the high, piercing tongue of the bat.
   PLREVENT 0
   CONTPLREVENT
   IFVAR TIM > 4
    IFVAR TIM < 20
     ECHO PLAYER You feel the slumbering thoughts of Bat, powerless in the daylight.
    ELSE
     ECHO PLAYER You are filled with the flying power of Bat.
     SPELL 224 0
    ENDIF
   ELSE
    ECHO PLAYER You are filled with the flying power of Bat.
    SPELL 224 0
   ENDIF
  ENDIF
 IFVAR INTNUM57 = 10
   IFVAR ITEMVAL3 ! TIM
    ECHO PLAYER You beseech stealthy Cat for his aid!
    ECHO OTHERS %n calls out in the purring tongue of the cat.
    SETITEMVAL -1 3 TIM
    PLREVENT 0
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER You are filled with the perception of Cat.
    SPELL 520 0
   ELSE
    ECHO PLAYER Nothing seems to happen.
   ENDIF
  ENDIF
 ELSE
  REMOVEITEM -1
  ECHO PLAYER You feel a sense of confusion as several primal spirits seem to gaze deep within you.
  ECHO OTHERS %n trembles and falls to %h knees in terror.
  POSITION KNEEL
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB RUB -1
 CLEARVERB
 IFVAR ITEMVAL2 = 1
   IFVAR INTNUM3 = 541 ;GUILDMASTER INTNUM3
     RANDOM SHROUDRUB 1 10 0
     IFVAR SHROUDRUB = 1
       ECHO ALL A chorus of howling wolves rises about the area in an ascending crescendo.
     ENDIF
     IFVAR SHROUDRUB = 2
       ECHO ALL With a muted flapping sound, a flock of ravens wheels overhead.
     ENDIF
     IFVAR SHROUDRUB = 3
       ECHO ALL On silent wings, a shadowy owl sweeps past low overhead.
     ENDIF
     IFVAR SHROUDRUB = 4
       ECHO PLAYER Suddenly a myriad of animal sounds fills the air about you, enfolding you in their comforting embrace.
       ECHO OTHERS %N suddenly smiles, and closes %h eyes as the air fills with a myriad of animal and bird sounds. 
     ENDIF
     IFVAR SHROUDRUB = 5
       ECHO PLAYER A mighty eagle stoops to land on your shoulder, before promptly spreading its mighty wings and taking to the air once again.
       ECHO OTHERS A mighty eagle stoops to land on %n's shoulder, before promptly spreading its mighty wings and taking to the air once again.
     ENDIF
     IFVAR SHROUDRUB = 6
       ECHO ALL With a clatter of hooves, a magnificent deer bursts into view, then bounds quickly out of sight.
     ENDIF
     IFVAR SHROUDRUB = 7
       ECHO PLAYER A swirling gyre of bats wings its way out of the sky to swirl about you, then spirals off into the distance.
       ECHO OTHERS A swirling gyre of bats wings its way out of the sky to swirl about %n, then spirals off into the distance.
     ENDIF
     IFVAR SHROUDRUB = 8
       ECHO ALL The defiant snort of a mighty boar sounds from somewhere nearby.
     ENDIF
     IFVAR SHROUDRUB = 9
       ECHO ALL A sibilant rustling sound heralds the passage of several serpents as they pass swiftly by.
     ENDIF
     IFVAR SHROUDRUB = 10
       ECHO ALL The deep throated cough of a great cat slashes through the air.
     ENDIF
   ELSE 
     REMOVEITEM -1
     ECHO ALL The shroud dissolves in a cloud of black smoke.
   ENDIF
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB CONCENTRATE -1
 CLEARVERB
 IFVAR ITEMVAL1 = INTNUM3
  IFVAR INTNUM57 = 0
   ECHO PLAYER You send your soul out to the spirits of the wood with no visible response.
   ECHO OTHERS As the smells of the forest seem to blow through the area on the wings of a gentle breeze, 
   ECHO OTHERS %n throws %h shoulders back as if trying to escape the bounds of flesh before returning to %iself with a shudder.                                                                      
  ENDIF
  IFVAR INTNUM57 = 1
   ECHO PLAYER You cast your thoughts out to Wolf.
   PLREVENT 0
   CONTPLREVENT
   ECHO ALL A chorus of howling wolves rises about the area in an ascending crescendo.
  ENDIF
  IFVAR INTNUM57 = 2
   ECHO PLAYER You cast your thoughts out to Raven.
   PLREVENT 0
   CONTPLREVENT
   ECHO ALL With a muted flapping sound, a flock of ravens wheels overhead.
  ENDIF
  IFVAR INTNUM57 = 4
   ECHO PLAYER You cast your thoughts out to Falcon.
   PLREVENT 0
   CONTPLREVENT
   ECHO ALL The piercing cry of a hunting falcon sounds high above you.
  ENDIF
  IFVAR INTNUM57 = 7
   ECHO PLAYER You cast your thoughts out to Bat.
   PLREVENT 0
   CONTPLREVENT
   ECHO PLAYER A swirling gyre of bats wings its way out of the sky to swirl about you, then spirals off into the distance.
   ECHO OTHERS A swirling gyre of bats wings its way out of the sky to swirl about %n, then spirals off into the distance.
  ENDIF
  IFVAR INTNUM57 = 10
   ECHO PLAYER You cast your thoughts out to Cat.
   PLREVENT 0
   CONTPLREVENT
   ECHO ALL The deep throated cough of a great cat slashes through the air.
  ENDIF
 ELSE
  REMOVEITEM -1
  ECHO PLAYER You feel a sense of confusion as several primal spirits seem to gaze deep within you.
  ECHO OTHERS %n trembles and falls to %h knees in terror.
  POSITION KNEEL
 ENDIF
ENDIF
