NUMBER 2441
NAME The Top of the Tree, Council Chamber
FOREST
CALL 33
REGION 151
*DESCRIPTION_START
The interwoven latticework of tiny branches continues, rising up in front of you to form a wall, set into which is a door inscribed with a name. The Guildmaster of Tiewaz Y'Perth. A large circular table surrounded by intricately carved, high-backed chairs sits in the center of this chamber. To the north, you can return to the training area and to the southwest the boughs of the tree open up to form a terrace. Through the canopy of lattice within the structure of the great oaks chutes you can see the expanse of the everlasting sky spread out in all directions to watch over the land below.
*DESCRIPTION_END
FIXED_LIGHT
ITEM 2 65  VAL1=1000 VAL2=2444 VAL3=2444
ITEM 3 91  ADJ1=178 ADJ2=693
ITEM 4 86  ADJ1=695 ADJ2=46 ADJ3=1283
ITEM 5 86  ADJ1=695 ADJ2=46 ADJ3=1283
ITEM 9 693
EXTEND 2 inscribed with the name 'Mokiah'
EXIT N 2437
EXIT SW 2442
IFPREVERB CALL -1
 CLEARVERB
 ECHO PLAYER Your voice cannot reach the woodlands here.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB SNEAK -1
 IFVAR ORG ! 27
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You can't seem to do that.
  ECHO OTHERS You notice %n acting rather suspicious.
 ENDIF
ENDIF
