NUMBER 2445
NAME Beneath the Tree, Hidden Cavern
CALL 33
CAVE
REGION 151
LOOM
*DESCRIPTION_START
The soft black soil gives way glittering limestone walls and a sparkling, polished marble floor. Sedementary deposits filtering down from the stream above have formed a multitude of luminescent green, limestone columns. Various craftspeople and artisans have arranged working spaces within the forest of limestone columns.  A merchant lists wares for sale on a small, handcarved sign. A loom clacks away merrily at the far end of the chamber just past where a healer has set out woven mats for her patients. An opening leads back through the roots of the tree and two arches of natural limestone lead to workshops. A statue in relief seems to step out of the far wall towards you.
*DESCRIPTION_END
